### 5. **AOI Service Pattern - Alternative Approach**

**Location**: `S:\01_Repos\BeFirst_APIs\BeFirst_APIs\Service\AOI\`

This service uses **raw SQL instead of DbContext**:

**IAOIService.cs**:
```csharp
public interface IAOIService
{
    Task<AOIDataResponse> SubmitInspectionAsync(AOIDataRequest request);
    Task<AOIBatchResponse> SubmitInspectionBatchAsync(List<AOIDataRequest> requests);
    Task<AOIMachineConfig?> GetMachineConfigAsync(int aoiId);
}
```

**AOIService.cs**:
```csharp
public class AOIService : IAOIService
{
    private readonly IConfiguration _configuration;
    private readonly string _connectionString;

    public AOIService(IConfiguration configuration)
    {
        _configuration = configuration;
        _connectionString = _configuration.GetConnectionString("MES")
            ?? throw new InvalidOperationException("MES connection string not found");
    }

    public async Task<AOIDataResponse> SubmitInspectionAsync(AOIDataRequest request)
    {
        using (var connection = new SqlConnection(_connectionString))
        {
            await connection.OpenAsync();

            var insertQuery = @"
                INSERT INTO Machines_Extractor_AOI_Data
                (AOIID, StationID, PartNumber, PartID, Side, SerialNumber, 
                 Position, Result, Operator, InspectionDate, DefectCodeID, CreatedDate)
                VALUES (@AOIID, @StationID, @PartNumber, @PartID, @Side, @SerialNumber,
                        @Position, @Result, @Operator, @InspectionDate, @DefectCodeID, GETDATE());
                SELECT SCOPE_IDENTITY();";

            using (var command = new SqlCommand(insertQuery, connection))
            {
                command.Parameters.AddWithValue("@AOIID", request.AOIID);
                // ... other parameters
                var mainRecordId = await command.ExecuteScalarAsync();
                // ... additional processing
            }
        }
    }
}
```

**Key Differences**:
- Does NOT inherit from ModelBase
- Receives IConfiguration, extracts connection string
- Uses SqlConnection and SqlCommand (raw ADO.NET)
- Handles parameterized queries manually
- More control over transaction-like behavior
- Direct INSERT/UPDATE statements

