### Summary of Key Patterns

| Pattern | Details |
|---------|---------|
| **Lifetime** | All services use Scoped lifetime (per-request) |
| **Inheritance** | Services typically inherit from ModelBase for standard DI |
| **DbContext** | Multiple contexts available: ProdMesDbContext, ProdMachinesResultsContext, etc. |
| **Constructor DI** | All dependencies injected via constructor, not property injection |
| **Async/Await** | All database operations are async (Task-based) |
| **Error Handling** | Try-catch at controller/service level with appropriate HTTP status codes |
| **Validation** | DataAnnotations on request models, ModelState checked in controllers |
| **Logging** | ILogger<T> injected for structured logging at controller level |
| **Response Objects** | Typed response objects returned, not anonymous types |
| **SQL Patterns** | Two approaches: Entity Framework (DbContext) or raw SQL (SqlConnection) |
| **Swagger Docs** | ProducesResponseType attributes for endpoint documentation |

